The Cape Town music promoter has admitted to shooting dead Toufiq Joseph in Gardens in 2015 but claims it was in self-defence. CAPE TOWN - A Cape Town music festival promoter will stand trial in June for murder.David Forbes, who has admitted to shooting dead Toufiq Joseph in Gardens in 2015, appeared briefly in the Cape Town Regional Court on Monday. He claims he shot Joseph in self-defence.Forbes' defence team and the State have concluded all pre-trial formalities.They've told the court they will be ready to proceed with the trial in June. The defence had previously tried to convince the State to change the murder charge to one of culpable homicide. It's argued Forbes shot Josephs when the 23-year-old attacked him with a knife.But the State is adamant that the businessman must stand trial for murder.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)